---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="container">

      <section class="hero">
        <h1>About Us</h1>
      </section>

      <section class="about">
        <h2>Why this blog exists</h2>
        <p>
          Mind the Gael exists because female athletes in Ladies Gaelic Football deserve mental health resources tailored to their experience. Many players still face stigma, lack guidance on mental wellbeing in sport, and miss evidence-based psychology tools that are specific to their team culture and performance needs.
        </p>

        <h2>Problem we’re solving</h2>
        <p>
          We’re solving the gap between traditional sport psychology and the real-world needs of women players. Rather than one-size-fits-all advice, we provide practical strategies to help athletes manage stress, maintain focus, and build strong team identity under pressure.
        </p>

        <h2>What you’ll find here</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Sports psychology explanation and application</li>
          <li>Performance mindset training exercises</li>
          <li>Team dynamics and cohesion strategies</li>
          <li>Actionable insights from current research</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who it’s for</h2>
        <p>
          This is for Ladies Gaelic Football players, coaches, and support staff who want to improve mental performance, reduce anxiety, and build confidence on and off the field. It is also useful for sports psychologists working with grassroots teams.
        </p>

        <h2>Start here</h2>
        <div class="start-buttons">
          <a href="/blog/training-the-mind/" class="start-button">Training the Mind</a>
          <a href="/blog/gael-performance-toolkit/" class="start-button">Gael Performance Toolkit</a>
          <a href="/blog/strong-minds-stronger-players/" class="start-button">Strong Minds, Stronger Players</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  h1 {
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  h2 {
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: #f0cdff;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .about p,
  .honest p,
  .what-we-build p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .honest {
    border-left: 3px solid #69005a;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .what-we-build ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .what-we-build ul li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .about ul {
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .closing {
    color: #f0cdff;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .start-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .start-button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.2rem;
    background-color: var(--green-lime);
    color: var(--green-dark);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .start-button:hover {
    background-color: var(--purple-light);
    border-color: var(--purple);
    color: var(--green-dark);
  }
</style>
